---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import SectionHead from '../components/SectionHead.astro';
---
<Base title="About — Acme Coffee & Roasters">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero__eyebrow-row">
      <span class="eyebrow">About</span>
    </div>
    <h1 class="hero__title">Two roasters, <em>one</em> drum.</h1>
    <p class="hero__lede">
      Acme started in 2018 in a converted bakery garage. The drum roaster came
      from an auction in Des Moines, Iowa. The name came from a kid's lunchbox.
    </p>
  </section>

  <SectionHead kicker="Philosophy" title="What we believe about roast." />
  <div class="container">
    <div class="prose">
      <p class="dropcap">
        We don't roast past medium. Light-to-medium holds more of what the farm
        did — the acidity, the fruit, the character you paid for. If you want a
        French roast, there are plenty of shops in town that'll do that better
        than we will.
      </p>

      <blockquote class="pullquote">
        We'd rather short a week than send something we don't stand behind.
      </blockquote>

      <p>
        Every lot gets cupped before we release it. If a bag isn't what we
        thought it'd be, it goes back or gets blended.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <SectionHead kicker="The two of us" title="Who's here." />
  <div class="container">
    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        <strong>Dana</strong> runs the roaster and the books.
        <strong>Mike</strong> runs the bar and the wholesale accounts.
        Saturdays you'll usually see both of us.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <SectionHead kicker="Sourcing" title="Where we buy from." />
  <div class="container">
    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        We buy green coffee through two importers — one in Oakland, one in
        Brooklyn. Whenever we can trace a lot back to a named farm or
        cooperative, we put that on the bag. Some weeks that's most of what we
        have; some weeks it's none of it. We'll tell you when it's which.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
